WEBVTT

00:40.301 --> 00:41.998
[indistinct chatter
in distant hallway]

01:09.025 --> 01:09.895
[door opens]

01:11.158 --> 01:13.377
[running footsteps]

01:13.421 --> 01:15.684
- [boy] Come on.
Pass, pass. I'm open.
- [man] A little slower
in the hallway, please.

01:15.727 --> 01:18.817
-[boy 2] You're an idiot.
-[girl] What if no one asks me?
Like last year?

01:18.861 --> 01:21.255
-[boy 3] I'll get that, milady.
-[laughter]

01:21.298 --> 01:23.648
-[school bell ringing]
-[indistinct chatter]

01:30.351 --> 01:31.961
[chatter continues]

01:35.530 --> 01:36.531
[door opens]

01:38.098 --> 01:40.100
[piano music playing]

01:43.015 --> 01:44.365
[chuckles softly]

01:44.408 --> 01:46.149
[girl] You didn't tell me
you played piano.

01:46.889 --> 01:47.890
[Maren] Hey.

01:49.805 --> 01:51.633
You are here.
Where have you been?

01:51.676 --> 01:53.287
You weren't in Home Ec.
all week.

01:53.330 --> 01:55.158
I got to slip to work
on the yearbook.

01:55.202 --> 01:56.855
We missed our deadline
with Jostens.

01:56.899 --> 01:58.248
Oh. How's it look?

01:59.989 --> 02:01.773
You're not gonna be in it,
by the way.

02:01.817 --> 02:03.514
Mr. Esser said
he reminded you three times

02:03.558 --> 02:05.429
-to get your picture taken.
-[plays piano]

02:07.736 --> 02:09.433
Hey, so my dad's doing
inventory all night,

02:09.477 --> 02:11.348
and Kim and Jackie
are sleeping over.

02:11.827 --> 02:12.654
Come too.

02:13.829 --> 02:15.526
[continues playing piano]

02:15.570 --> 02:17.659
No, my dad won't let me.

02:17.702 --> 02:19.791
So sneak out.
After he goes to bed.

02:21.489 --> 02:22.533
How would I get there?

02:23.665 --> 02:24.970
You're down
in Southwind, right?

02:26.233 --> 02:27.538
You know the power lines
that go up the hill?

02:28.931 --> 02:31.151
That's Chesapeake Road
at the top. I'm right there.

02:33.109 --> 02:34.458
You said you wanna make
more friends here.

02:37.418 --> 02:39.289
[students chattering]

02:42.858 --> 02:44.990
Hey. Come on, you drive.

02:45.034 --> 02:46.514
-[boy] Okay.
-[girl] Take care. Bye.

03:10.929 --> 03:12.714
[men laughing and chattering]

03:16.674 --> 03:18.981
Hey. That was good
on the road.

03:20.548 --> 03:22.114
Gotta work on that parking
some more...

03:23.203 --> 03:24.073
but good.

03:31.515 --> 03:32.690
You think
it's gonna rain tonight?

03:34.518 --> 03:35.954
Don't think it's supposed to.

03:43.353 --> 03:44.441
[can pops open]

03:47.705 --> 03:49.707
[grunts] Got homework?

03:51.622 --> 03:52.623
Just reading, Dad.

03:54.103 --> 03:56.453
The man has attempted suicide.

03:56.497 --> 03:58.020
I think he realized

03:58.063 --> 04:01.545
that this scheme that
he had been involved in,

04:01.589 --> 04:04.679
about which he had
always been extremely guilty.

04:04.722 --> 04:07.812
I mean, he's... he's,
I think, the only person

04:07.856 --> 04:13.035
in this entire scheme to have
voluntarily walked out on it.

04:13.078 --> 04:16.865
Some people were annoyed
with it, upset with it,

04:16.908 --> 04:19.607
and... but went along with it.
Others enjoyed it

04:19.650 --> 04:21.522
because they were making
a lot of money out of it.

04:21.565 --> 04:25.700
Dowd was the only person
who had the character...

04:26.570 --> 04:27.876
'Night, Dad.

04:27.919 --> 04:29.356
[man on TV]
...and the moral fiber...

04:29.399 --> 04:30.792
Yeah. Sleep good.

04:30.835 --> 04:32.141
[man on TV]
...to walk out on this scheme

04:32.184 --> 04:33.534
long before anybody
knew about it,

04:33.577 --> 04:35.144
because it disgusted him.

04:35.187 --> 04:38.756
I mean,
the prospect of actually

04:38.800 --> 04:40.802
walking into
Donald Manes' office

04:40.845 --> 04:42.020
and paying him cash...

04:59.081 --> 05:01.083
[wind blowing]

05:25.107 --> 05:27.065
-[muffled music playing]
-[muffled chatter]

05:29.807 --> 05:31.243
[panting]

05:38.033 --> 05:39.121
Hang on. Okay.

05:42.385 --> 05:43.255
-Hey.
-Hey.

05:45.736 --> 05:48.304
You got prickers all over you.
Come in.

05:51.133 --> 05:52.961
[indistinct chatter]

05:55.050 --> 05:56.356
[Kim] So you can't
spend the night?

05:57.574 --> 05:58.967
[Maren] Not all night.

05:59.010 --> 06:00.751
I should be back
by 6:00 to be safe.

06:02.057 --> 06:03.406
Jesus.

06:03.450 --> 06:05.800
I'll just head out
when you guys wanna sleep.

06:08.629 --> 06:10.021
So where'd you move here
from anyway?

06:11.501 --> 06:12.546
Eastern shore.

06:14.461 --> 06:15.549
Is your mom in the picture?

06:18.160 --> 06:19.944
Sherry says
you only have a dad.

06:19.988 --> 06:21.206
[knock on table]

06:22.904 --> 06:24.384
"Cinnamon Glaze."

06:25.776 --> 06:26.777
We're trying to talk.

06:31.129 --> 06:32.304
[Sherry] Kim,
give me your hand.

06:39.529 --> 06:41.401
[Kim] Never mind
about your mom.

06:41.444 --> 06:43.315
It's none of my business,
anyway.

06:45.796 --> 06:47.407
[inhales deeply]

06:48.451 --> 06:50.410
I don't have
any memories of her.

06:52.020 --> 06:53.238
Or photos even.

06:55.066 --> 06:56.851
My dad wouldn't
tell me anything.

07:00.463 --> 07:02.813
Try that.
It's called "Copper Fever."

07:05.555 --> 07:06.730
It's too orange.

07:16.087 --> 07:18.394
-[bones crunching]
-[screaming]

07:20.396 --> 07:21.441
Oh, my God!

07:21.484 --> 07:22.964
Maren, stop it!

07:23.007 --> 07:24.487
Stop! Stop it!

07:24.531 --> 07:26.794
Maren, stop! Maren, no!

07:26.837 --> 07:27.751
-Jackie!
-[continues screaming]

07:27.795 --> 07:28.883
Maren, stop!

07:30.450 --> 07:32.626
Jackie! Jackie, help!

07:33.365 --> 07:34.454
Jackie, help!

07:36.107 --> 07:37.544
[panting]

07:51.558 --> 07:53.560
[banging on door]

07:56.693 --> 07:57.607
You didn't.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.569
In the car in three minutes.

08:02.612 --> 08:04.222
Whatever you can take
in three minutes.

08:05.920 --> 08:06.834
Go!

08:08.444 --> 08:09.619
Shit.

08:16.017 --> 08:17.540
Move, Maren!

08:17.584 --> 08:19.890
When the cops get here,
we have to be good and gone.

08:58.886 --> 08:59.756
Dad?

09:02.367 --> 09:03.238
[sighs]

09:04.631 --> 09:05.632
[yawning]

09:14.292 --> 09:15.119
Dad?

09:25.390 --> 09:27.131
[breathing heavily]

10:04.168 --> 10:04.995
[button clicks]

10:08.042 --> 10:09.696
[Maren's father on tape]
I've got some things to say.

10:09.739 --> 10:10.610
And then...

10:12.089 --> 10:14.657
I want you to make sure
this, uh...

10:14.701 --> 10:16.877
this tape is good
and destroyed. Don't keep it.

10:18.052 --> 10:19.183
This has got my voice on it.

10:20.968 --> 10:22.970
You're not going
to see me again, Maren.

10:26.756 --> 10:27.670
I can't...

10:30.673 --> 10:31.631
help you anymore.

10:31.674 --> 10:33.850
[Maren crying]

10:33.894 --> 10:36.810
I can't do anything else,
either.

10:36.853 --> 10:40.727
Call the cops or whatever
somebody might do in my place.

10:42.772 --> 10:44.992
So I gotta leave you
to figure it out for yourself.

10:46.210 --> 10:47.995
Like your mother did.

10:48.038 --> 10:50.562
I'm sorry. You know
what I mean now.

10:51.738 --> 10:53.348
I don't know how much...

10:53.391 --> 10:56.568
how much of what I'm gonna say
you'll remember.

10:57.918 --> 11:00.660
[sighs] Yeah. Never was sure.

11:01.356 --> 11:03.227
But just in case,

11:03.271 --> 11:04.664
I'll tell you
everything I know.

11:06.753 --> 11:08.450
First time was
when you were three.

11:12.976 --> 11:15.283
[indistinct talking on TV]

11:15.326 --> 11:17.154
[newscaster]
Downey has the crowd screaming

11:17.198 --> 11:18.895
at Towson State University.

11:18.939 --> 11:20.984
The topic was
the most controversial issue

11:21.028 --> 11:22.725
on this year's
Maryland ballot,

11:22.769 --> 11:24.161
the gun ban referendum.

11:24.205 --> 11:25.641
The majority of those
in the audience

11:25.685 --> 11:27.251
seem to be against the ban,

11:27.295 --> 11:28.775
but we found those
on both sides of the issue.

11:28.818 --> 11:30.124
[woman] I think
it's a good law,

11:30.167 --> 11:31.603
if she gets
guns off the streets,

11:31.647 --> 11:33.518
and that's what we need most.

11:33.562 --> 11:35.172
[man] I just
don't think it's fair

11:35.216 --> 11:37.044
for all the innocent people
that wanna get a gun

11:37.087 --> 11:39.089
to protect themselves.

11:39.133 --> 11:42.484
Just making it easier for
criminals to have them than
honest people.

11:42.527 --> 11:45.226
[man 2] I don't want them comin'
in my living room and tell me
what I can and can't buy.

11:45.269 --> 11:46.967
Y'all think if you take
the guns away from everybody,

11:47.010 --> 11:49.056
you have less shooting
with the whole nine-yards,

11:49.099 --> 11:51.101
the criminals
and the innocent people.

11:58.326 --> 11:59.327
Hi.

12:00.023 --> 12:00.850
Uh...

12:02.722 --> 12:03.723
I need to get here.

12:05.986 --> 12:07.683
What's the closest
I can get by bus?

12:07.727 --> 12:10.338
Well, looks like
Detroit Lakes.

12:13.689 --> 12:15.473
Three transfers.

12:15.517 --> 12:19.260
Frederick, Maryland,
Columbus and Minneapolis.

12:21.044 --> 12:23.220
One way? 83.

12:25.048 --> 12:26.441
How much to Columbus?

12:29.879 --> 12:31.663
Shouldn't you be in school?

12:32.926 --> 12:34.362
You'd think.

12:34.405 --> 12:35.929
I don't know what that means.

12:37.800 --> 12:39.410
Means I'm 18,
in the state of Maryland,

12:39.454 --> 12:41.369
and I can decide for myself
where I should be.

12:43.806 --> 12:46.940
I'm gonna need to see
a driver's license
or a learner's permit.

12:50.030 --> 12:51.466
You can see
a birth certificate.

12:54.469 --> 12:55.339
Come on.

13:05.088 --> 13:06.089
Just to Columbus?

13:06.655 --> 13:07.656
It's 49.

13:09.005 --> 13:09.876
50.

13:14.054 --> 13:15.838
[passengers chattering]

13:27.676 --> 13:29.243
[Maren's father]
I had a sitter for you then.

13:30.810 --> 13:32.333
[chuckles] Her name was Penny.

13:33.769 --> 13:35.989
When I came in,
she was on the bathroom floor.

13:36.032 --> 13:39.166
There was... so much blood.

13:40.645 --> 13:42.256
Her face was chewed up bad,

13:42.299 --> 13:46.390
but the worst of it
was her neck.

13:46.434 --> 13:49.872
She must've been holding you
when you started in on her.

13:49.916 --> 13:51.526
Her hands, all chewed up. I...

13:51.569 --> 13:54.877
I thought you were dead too.

13:54.921 --> 13:56.052
That somebody
had done you both,

13:56.096 --> 13:58.098
but you were sleepin'.

13:58.141 --> 14:00.448
When I turned you over,
I saw the blood on your mouth.

14:00.491 --> 14:04.887
You had something
in your cheek.

14:04.931 --> 14:07.890
I fished it out. It was soft,
like a wad of gum.

14:07.934 --> 14:09.457
It had a little hole in it.

14:10.501 --> 14:11.807
Where an earring would go.

14:14.331 --> 14:16.203
I remember thanking God
she hadn't been wearing any,

14:16.246 --> 14:17.204
you could've choked.

14:19.554 --> 14:20.816
I got the body out,

14:20.860 --> 14:22.122
I bleached the place
three times,

14:22.165 --> 14:23.427
and then packed us up
and left.

14:24.559 --> 14:25.995
They never found
where I put her.

14:27.823 --> 14:30.870
That was the last time
I used our real last name.

14:31.827 --> 14:33.829
Now you know why.

14:33.873 --> 14:36.136
Nothin' happened
for a few years. I relaxed.

14:37.485 --> 14:39.095
You had to start school
and I thought...

14:39.139 --> 14:41.184
I thought you wouldn't
do it in public,

14:41.228 --> 14:42.098
and you didn't.

14:43.143 --> 14:44.144
But you got clever.

14:45.275 --> 14:46.798
So fucking clever.

14:58.723 --> 14:59.899
[sighs]

14:59.942 --> 15:01.248
[thunder rumbling]

15:21.964 --> 15:23.923
[rain pattering]

15:38.502 --> 15:40.243
[thunder continues rumbling]

16:09.098 --> 16:11.057
I didn't mean to scare you.

16:11.883 --> 16:13.711
[breathing shakily]

16:15.104 --> 16:16.279
You waiting for the bus?

16:19.021 --> 16:20.805
Well, no, missy. I...

16:21.719 --> 16:23.417
I came lookin' for you.

16:27.334 --> 16:28.204
Do I know you?

16:30.685 --> 16:32.992
I guess not in the way
you mean.

16:36.299 --> 16:38.040
I smelled you.

16:38.084 --> 16:40.695
You probably smell me now.

16:42.088 --> 16:44.525
When was the last time
you fed?

16:46.701 --> 16:47.963
[thunder rumbling]

16:51.184 --> 16:52.707
[sniffs]

16:52.750 --> 16:54.970
[Maren] Stop, stop,
stop there. Stop.

16:58.060 --> 17:01.933
You haven't in a long time.
[sniffs]

17:01.977 --> 17:02.934
I'll say...

17:05.111 --> 17:06.373
many months.

17:07.591 --> 17:08.592
At least.

17:10.377 --> 17:11.856
You can smell that?

17:11.900 --> 17:13.771
[chuckles] Oh, sure.

17:14.468 --> 17:15.860
You can...

17:15.904 --> 17:19.734
You can smell lots of things
if you know how.

17:19.777 --> 17:20.604
[sniffs]

17:21.866 --> 17:25.044
And we just smell anyway.
[laughs]

17:26.175 --> 17:28.438
Whether we ate or not.

17:50.330 --> 17:51.200
Hmm.

17:59.165 --> 18:00.166
Come on, missy.

18:02.864 --> 18:03.691
Come on.

18:13.788 --> 18:14.615
Come on.

18:19.315 --> 18:21.056
[Maren] Where are we goin'?

18:21.100 --> 18:23.537
Just here,
someplace dry and safe.

18:25.234 --> 18:26.366
I'm Sullivan.

18:27.758 --> 18:29.325
Friends call me Sully.

18:30.892 --> 18:31.762
Maren.

18:33.503 --> 18:34.548
Is this your house?

18:36.985 --> 18:38.552
Listen, Maren,

18:38.595 --> 18:40.684
don't worry. I'm okay.

18:41.772 --> 18:43.165
I got rules.

18:43.818 --> 18:45.559
One, number one

18:45.602 --> 18:49.389
is never, never, ever
eat an Eater.

18:49.432 --> 18:51.130
Think you can follow that too?

18:52.783 --> 18:53.915
All right.

18:53.958 --> 18:55.786
I'll fix some dinner for us.

18:58.311 --> 19:02.489
I smelled you from the yard,
little missy. Come on.

19:03.142 --> 19:04.099
This far?

19:05.796 --> 19:08.364
[Sully] Round the back.
We'll talk inside.

19:40.396 --> 19:44.183
The Sully, he found
these little Cornish hens

19:45.706 --> 19:46.707
in the freezer.

19:48.752 --> 19:50.014
These hens,

19:51.668 --> 19:53.670
they look like
they had a good life.

20:00.242 --> 20:01.591
Thought I was the only one.

20:03.289 --> 20:04.855
Are there lots of us?

20:04.899 --> 20:05.943
Not lots.

20:06.901 --> 20:08.555
But more...

20:09.991 --> 20:11.775
more than you'd think.

20:11.819 --> 20:14.778
You've met a few, sure,
that you know of.

20:15.823 --> 20:17.172
[bones snapping]

20:17.216 --> 20:21.132
You never had anyone
take a interest in you?

20:21.176 --> 20:23.744
[stutters] A double take?

20:23.787 --> 20:24.788
[chuckles]

20:25.876 --> 20:27.095
Just always thought--

20:27.138 --> 20:31.665
You just thought
some people are creepy.

20:31.708 --> 20:36.409
It's better if we all
steer clear of one another.

20:37.453 --> 20:39.629
We're dangerous to non-Eaters,

20:39.673 --> 20:44.634
but we can hurt
one another just as bad.

20:44.678 --> 20:47.071
I hope you're
hearing me on this.

20:47.724 --> 20:48.943
[thunder rumbling]

20:50.336 --> 20:52.033
You sound like my dad.

20:52.076 --> 20:54.253
Your daddy find out about you?

20:59.693 --> 21:00.694
What about you?

21:02.348 --> 21:05.394
You basically just said
steer clear of people like us.

21:07.048 --> 21:08.789
But you came looking for me.

21:08.832 --> 21:10.269
[chuckling]

21:10.312 --> 21:11.661
Smart.

21:13.272 --> 21:17.145
When I saw you're just
a girl on your own,

21:19.234 --> 21:20.061
I thought...

21:22.890 --> 21:24.413
you might be hungry.

21:27.242 --> 21:28.243
For hens?

21:30.071 --> 21:31.899
[breathing heavily]

21:34.902 --> 21:36.251
No.

21:56.315 --> 21:57.359
Who lives here?

21:59.535 --> 22:00.971
Well, go and look.

22:11.112 --> 22:12.896
[Maren sniffing]

22:14.202 --> 22:15.595
Use your nose.

22:16.596 --> 22:17.858
What do you smell?

22:19.425 --> 22:20.513
Is there someone
dead up there?

22:21.122 --> 22:22.645
What do you smell?

22:24.081 --> 22:25.387
Describe it.

22:29.435 --> 22:30.349
Metallic.

22:32.829 --> 22:34.091
Like blood?

22:37.181 --> 22:38.444
No, like mud.

22:41.795 --> 22:43.100
Something tangy.

22:45.712 --> 22:48.236
But not like rotten.

22:49.933 --> 22:50.804
No.

22:54.634 --> 22:55.635
But close.

22:56.592 --> 22:58.377
More like vinegar.

23:00.770 --> 23:03.251
Like vinegar in the soup.

23:04.383 --> 23:06.907
Yeah. Yeah.

23:17.396 --> 23:18.658
[Maren sniffing]

23:36.371 --> 23:38.895
[breathing laboriously]

23:38.939 --> 23:40.767
-She's alive.
-[Sully] Missy.

23:40.810 --> 23:42.290
-We'll get help.
-Missy.

23:42.333 --> 23:43.509
What did you do to her?

23:43.552 --> 23:45.424
I found her like that
this mornin'.

23:45.467 --> 23:47.426
You're lying. Let me by.

23:47.469 --> 23:50.211
Listen.
Let me bone down on this.

23:51.038 --> 23:52.431
Whatever you and I got,

23:53.214 --> 23:54.781
it's gotta be fed.

23:54.824 --> 23:56.435
[breathing shakily]

23:58.219 --> 23:59.394
No. Uh...

24:00.874 --> 24:02.397
No, 'cause it was...

24:04.181 --> 24:06.749
It was years
before my last time.

24:06.793 --> 24:09.099
[sighs]
That's because you're young.

24:11.275 --> 24:14.148
You're gonna need it
more and more,

24:14.191 --> 24:16.672
-and more and more.
-[whimpering]

24:16.716 --> 24:21.068
And you won't always be able
to hold yourself back.

24:21.111 --> 24:23.462
But if the circumstances is...

24:24.027 --> 24:26.029
is safe and good,

24:27.248 --> 24:28.336
then eat.

24:29.555 --> 24:31.078
It'll last a while,

24:31.121 --> 24:33.994
maybe it'll keep you from,

24:34.037 --> 24:36.431
you know,
doing something you'll regret.

24:38.694 --> 24:40.696
[Maren continues whimpering]

24:41.131 --> 24:42.393
Even more.

24:43.656 --> 24:45.048
Even more, missy.

24:48.617 --> 24:50.532
Yes, Sully found her that way.

24:51.402 --> 24:52.621
I followed my nose.

24:56.625 --> 24:58.888
I don't...
I don't kill people.

25:01.500 --> 25:03.110
At least I try not to.

25:06.200 --> 25:07.593
That leaves this.

25:10.030 --> 25:12.380
-And things like it.
-[sniffles]

25:20.606 --> 25:21.563
[sniffles]

25:24.174 --> 25:26.089
Can I have
a few minutes, please?

25:26.133 --> 25:27.177
Sure, you can.

25:31.617 --> 25:34.576
I don't think
it'll be a long time now.

25:34.620 --> 25:37.100
When the time comes,
you'll smell it.

25:40.539 --> 25:42.410
[woman breathing laboriously]

26:03.692 --> 26:05.302
[woman gagging]

26:07.783 --> 26:09.089
[stops breathing]

26:11.700 --> 26:13.006
[sniffling]

26:16.618 --> 26:18.881
-[soft footsteps]
-[Sully breathing heavily]

26:24.713 --> 26:25.627
[Sully clears throat]

26:28.499 --> 26:31.764
-[body being dragged]
-[Sully grunting]

26:33.330 --> 26:34.244
[body thuds]

26:39.162 --> 26:41.164
-[sniffs]
-[Sully coughing]

26:42.470 --> 26:45.560
[crunching and slurping]

26:59.922 --> 27:01.358
[Maren breathes excitedly]

27:02.664 --> 27:04.144
[both slurping and munching]

27:18.288 --> 27:19.289
[yawning]

27:37.656 --> 27:38.569
[groans]

27:45.228 --> 27:46.099
[sniffs]

27:46.142 --> 27:47.709
This is how I do it.

27:49.189 --> 27:52.496
It helps me
to remember each one.

27:52.540 --> 27:56.065
When I began this,
I was about your age.

28:00.026 --> 28:01.244
Pull it.

28:02.506 --> 28:03.682
You won't break it.

28:07.598 --> 28:08.425
[chuckles]

28:10.384 --> 28:12.734
It's strong. [laughs]

28:12.778 --> 28:15.302
[Maren] Who was your first?
You remember?

28:18.392 --> 28:20.133
I ate my own granddad

28:22.135 --> 28:24.398
while they were waiting
on the undertaker.

28:26.313 --> 28:28.924
Did anyone find you
while you were doing it?

28:28.968 --> 28:30.099
My mama.

28:31.884 --> 28:33.973
My mama found me afterwards.

28:35.061 --> 28:36.105
Cleaned me up.

28:38.673 --> 28:42.111
She told everyone
animals got in and did it.

28:42.155 --> 28:45.027
But when I finally ran off,

28:46.420 --> 28:48.727
no one came looking for me.

28:54.384 --> 28:56.735
[Maren] And you've been
on your own since then?

29:01.914 --> 29:03.002
It's not hard...

29:05.700 --> 29:07.223
once someone teaches you.

29:08.572 --> 29:09.486
[sniffs]

29:11.358 --> 29:13.360
But you don't...
you don't, uh...

29:14.753 --> 29:16.450
you don't need to be alone.

29:17.843 --> 29:20.454
You can bond with me
as long as you like.

29:25.111 --> 29:26.765
I'm looking for someone.

29:29.593 --> 29:30.638
Your mama.

29:31.726 --> 29:33.641
You mentioned
your daddy last night,

29:33.684 --> 29:34.990
so I knew he was
in the picture.

29:35.034 --> 29:36.731
You must be runnin' from him

29:37.906 --> 29:39.473
or he left you or somethin'.

29:39.516 --> 29:40.953
[flies buzzing]

29:40.996 --> 29:43.869
But you didn't say nothin'
about your mama, though.

29:45.871 --> 29:46.959
I never met her.

29:49.004 --> 29:51.702
All I have is the name of
the town she was born in.

29:51.746 --> 29:53.400
It's on my birth certificate.

29:53.443 --> 29:54.488
Mm-hmm.

29:55.663 --> 29:57.404
We better clean up

29:57.447 --> 30:00.537
before we dry stuck
to these chairs.

30:01.495 --> 30:03.627
-[flies continue buzzing]
-[grunts]

30:24.910 --> 30:30.045
[Sully singing]
♪ Beautiful,
beautiful brown eyes

30:30.089 --> 30:34.223
♪ Beautiful, beautiful brown

30:34.267 --> 30:36.356
[flies continue buzzing]

30:39.098 --> 30:43.015
♪ Beautiful,
beautiful brown eyes♪

30:45.887 --> 30:47.628
[men chattering]

31:13.132 --> 31:14.611
[Maren's father]
The next few, I didn't see.

31:16.309 --> 31:18.485
A boy went missin'
at a camp you went to.

31:18.528 --> 31:19.965
I shouldn't have let you go.

31:21.488 --> 31:23.229
But you wanted to.

31:23.272 --> 31:25.100
It was just a week.
You were eight.

31:27.059 --> 31:29.844
When that boy went missin',
I knew

31:29.888 --> 31:32.934
this is who you are.

31:32.978 --> 31:34.588
I never thought
"what" you are.

31:36.285 --> 31:38.853
I don't know if I loved you
the way a father should,

31:38.897 --> 31:40.420
but I... I didn't hate you.

31:41.551 --> 31:42.988
You...

31:43.031 --> 31:45.207
You ate them.
I believed you had to.

31:45.251 --> 31:46.252
I don't know why.

31:48.428 --> 31:51.213
They found his pup tent
pitched in the heavy woods,

31:51.257 --> 31:52.388
all bloody inside.

31:52.432 --> 31:55.130
Luke somethin' Vanderbilt.

31:55.174 --> 31:56.566
[driver on PA]
Good evening, everyone.

31:56.610 --> 31:57.785
[Maren's father]
They ruled it a homicide,

31:57.828 --> 31:59.178
I... I never heard.

31:59.221 --> 32:00.831
[driver] This is the end
of the line.

32:00.875 --> 32:02.355
[Maren's father] Vanderwall
or somethin' like that.

32:02.398 --> 32:03.965
[driver] Take all
your belongings with you.

32:04.009 --> 32:05.401
[Maren's father]
I watched after to see

32:05.445 --> 32:07.621
if you looked sad,
and you didn't.

32:09.231 --> 32:12.104
That was the beginnin'
of sayin' no to things.

32:14.106 --> 32:15.542
Now you know why
for that, too.

32:36.084 --> 32:37.999
[music playing on speakers]

32:38.043 --> 32:39.435
[man] So I was thinking...

32:43.309 --> 32:44.963
[indistinct chatter]

32:49.968 --> 32:50.925
[woman] No. It's not there.

32:52.057 --> 32:53.275
[indistinct chatter]

33:08.551 --> 33:10.901
You don't have Lunchables?

33:10.945 --> 33:12.381
What kind of
goddamned grocery store

33:12.425 --> 33:13.730
runs out of Lunchables?

33:18.866 --> 33:20.041
[woman 2] Excuse me.

33:20.085 --> 33:21.608
Whoa, you trying
to run me down?

33:22.739 --> 33:24.176
I asked a question.

33:24.219 --> 33:25.351
Hear this, you dumb ho.

33:25.394 --> 33:26.656
Hey, don't talk to her
like that!

33:26.700 --> 33:28.223
Hey!

33:28.267 --> 33:29.398
You're out of control, buddy.

33:31.705 --> 33:33.402
You with the store
or somethin'?

33:33.446 --> 33:34.664
No, I'm not with the store,

33:34.708 --> 33:36.057
but I'm gonna
escort you out of it.

33:36.101 --> 33:38.842
[chuckles]
Fucking see what happens.

33:38.886 --> 33:40.366
-See what happens?
-Yeah.

33:40.409 --> 33:41.367
What's gonna happen?
Something bad's gonna happen?

33:41.410 --> 33:43.673
Yeah.

33:43.717 --> 33:46.502
[laughs] Outside.
We're going outside.

33:46.546 --> 33:48.374
[boy] You enjoy
hassling people, man?

33:48.417 --> 33:49.636
Is that what you do
on Saturdays

33:49.679 --> 33:51.290
when you're done jerking off?

33:51.333 --> 33:54.162
[man 2] Hey, gimme my hat,
you little jackass.

34:21.407 --> 34:23.191
-[breathing heavily]
-[pensive music playing]

34:23.887 --> 34:25.063
[sniffling]

34:36.639 --> 34:38.467
[squelching]

34:54.179 --> 34:56.268
He's over in there, like,
400 yards if you wanna...

35:00.837 --> 35:02.317
[Maren] You could tell,
in the store?

35:04.232 --> 35:06.278
I smelled you too.
I didn't know I could do that.

35:08.236 --> 35:10.673
I'm, uh, going to Minnesota.

35:10.717 --> 35:14.286
I got dumped here by a ride.
I just stole dinner.

35:14.329 --> 35:15.417
It was all
I could think to do.

35:16.375 --> 35:18.072
You're not local either,
I guess.

35:18.116 --> 35:18.942
Why does that matter?

35:22.468 --> 35:24.513
That was nice what you did
for that mom in there.

35:27.473 --> 35:28.691
I'm 18, if you're wondering.

35:29.997 --> 35:31.129
I was gonna guess younger.

35:33.653 --> 35:34.480
Thanks.

35:36.090 --> 35:37.483
I don't usually talk
to anyone after.

35:37.526 --> 35:38.962
I don't actually meet
many others.

35:39.006 --> 35:39.963
Sort of glad not to.

35:40.007 --> 35:41.313
[Maren] Yeah, I get it.

35:41.356 --> 35:43.141
[boy] I'm just saying
I'm not an asshole.

35:45.969 --> 35:48.363
You should probably go anyway.
Up close, you can see blood.

35:50.974 --> 35:51.888
We're fine.

35:53.281 --> 35:54.195
No.

35:55.936 --> 35:57.329
I really don't think I am.

36:02.986 --> 36:03.987
You wanna get in for a minute?

36:16.217 --> 36:18.654
This truck's his.
You can't just take it.

36:18.698 --> 36:20.134
Everyone's got their rules.

36:21.309 --> 36:22.702
That's not one of my rules.

36:23.790 --> 36:25.487
"Barry Cook.

36:25.531 --> 36:29.578
"5278 Route 13.
Centerville, Indiana."

36:30.753 --> 36:31.928
You're going to his house?

36:34.017 --> 36:35.367
Yeah, he didn't have
any pictures in his wallet.
I think it'll be all right.

36:35.410 --> 36:36.890
-Took his wallet, too?
-I didn't take his wallet,

36:36.933 --> 36:39.109
I took the money
out of the wallet. Eight bucks.

36:39.153 --> 36:40.763
I chucked the wallet
in a creek back there.

36:46.378 --> 36:47.292
I'm Maren.

36:49.032 --> 36:49.946
I'm Lee.

36:51.557 --> 36:56.518
I don't know whether to cry,
or scream, or laugh, or what.

36:56.562 --> 36:57.476
Don't scream.

37:00.043 --> 37:01.436
I thought I was the only one.

37:02.698 --> 37:06.746
Now I meet two others
in a week.

37:08.269 --> 37:11.054
Hey, do you think
you could help me?

37:14.232 --> 37:16.277
-[sighs]
-I'm new at this.

37:16.321 --> 37:18.018
No one our age is new at this.

37:18.061 --> 37:19.846
Well, I'm new
at remembering it.

37:21.064 --> 37:23.153
At all.

37:23.197 --> 37:26.244
Look, I won't try to mess
with you. I promise.

37:26.287 --> 37:27.549
I don't wanna hurt anybody.

37:28.681 --> 37:30.770
-[Lee] Famous last words.
-[engine starts]

37:55.969 --> 37:57.187
[knocking on door]

37:57.927 --> 37:59.015
[door opens]

38:01.801 --> 38:02.802
[door closes]

38:23.736 --> 38:25.868
He's got Lick It Upby Kiss.

38:25.912 --> 38:27.479
That's the one where they stop
wearing make-up.

38:29.394 --> 38:30.264
Who?

38:31.439 --> 38:32.397
[Lee] You don't know
Lick It Up?

38:33.049 --> 38:34.747
You don't know Kiss?

38:34.790 --> 38:36.096
You were home-schooled,
I guess.

38:38.098 --> 38:40.318
Smells like he'd been getting
stoned in here for 30 years.

38:42.276 --> 38:45.497
Wait, this is it. He has it!
Lick It Up.

38:49.457 --> 38:50.545
["Lick It Up" by Kiss
plays loudly]

38:50.589 --> 38:51.503
Fuck.

38:52.808 --> 38:54.462
♪ Yeah, yeah♪

38:54.506 --> 38:55.463
You know?

38:58.292 --> 39:02.122
[sings along]
♪ Don't wanna wait
till you know me better♪

39:06.256 --> 39:09.956
♪ Let's just be glad
for the time together♪

39:14.264 --> 39:17.964
♪ Life's such a treat
And it's time you taste it♪

39:22.229 --> 39:26.233
♪ There ain't a reason on earth
to waste it♪

39:26.276 --> 39:29.932
♪ It ain't a crime
to be good to yourself♪

39:29.976 --> 39:30.933
♪ Lick it up♪

39:31.717 --> 39:33.022
♪ Lick it up♪

39:33.980 --> 39:36.156
♪ Oh, oh-oh!♪

39:36.199 --> 39:39.681
♪ It's only right now
Lick it up♪

39:39.725 --> 39:41.248
♪ Lick it up♪

39:42.902 --> 39:44.338
I'mma take a shower.

39:44.382 --> 39:45.905
♪ Yeah♪

39:45.948 --> 39:46.819
♪ Lick it up♪

39:47.689 --> 39:48.864
♪ Lick it up♪

39:49.865 --> 39:52.085
♪ Oh, oh-oh!♪

39:52.128 --> 39:53.869
♪ Come on,c ome on♪

39:53.913 --> 39:55.610
♪ Lick it up♪

39:55.654 --> 39:57.699
♪ Lick it up♪

39:57.743 --> 40:00.267
♪ Oh, oh-oh!♪

40:03.052 --> 40:04.706
[shower running]

40:10.103 --> 40:13.889
♪ Don't need to wait
for an invitation♪

40:17.850 --> 40:19.678
[indistinct tv chatter]

40:19.721 --> 40:21.854
[commentator 1 on TV]
Here comes Robert Ford there,

40:21.897 --> 40:23.943
interfering where
he's got no place.

40:26.728 --> 40:29.992
-Disqualification on Eric.
-[commentator 2] Yeah.

40:30.036 --> 40:32.908
Boyd jumps up in the ring.
Robs Jarrett.

40:32.952 --> 40:34.736
Keith Eric starts
to kick on him,

40:34.780 --> 40:37.652
and Fuller says no,
bam, and he throws...

40:41.177 --> 40:43.266
[eerie music playing]

40:46.444 --> 40:47.967
[Maren moaning softly]

40:54.103 --> 40:55.235
[Maren's father]
It's your birthday.

40:56.541 --> 41:00.283
I've been waiting on this day
for a long time.

41:00.327 --> 41:01.633
-[blows]
-[Maren gasps]

41:08.161 --> 41:10.032
[indistinct TV chatter]

41:11.947 --> 41:14.210
You seemed like
such a hardcase yesterday.

41:15.342 --> 41:17.562
When you weigh 140 pounds wet,

41:17.605 --> 41:18.737
you gotta have
a big attitude instead.

41:18.780 --> 41:19.825
I've got that for you.

41:19.868 --> 41:21.740
-And the pancakes.
-Thanks.

41:21.783 --> 41:22.915
-And your bacon.
-Thank you.

41:26.745 --> 41:28.224
Sully.

41:28.268 --> 41:29.791
That's his name.
The other guy I met.

41:30.705 --> 41:32.098
He showed up at a bus station

41:32.141 --> 41:34.448
saying he could smell me
half a mile away.

41:35.449 --> 41:37.538
-Can you do that?
-Not that far.

41:37.582 --> 41:38.713
Said he could also smell

41:38.757 --> 41:40.193
when people are
about to die too.

41:41.977 --> 41:43.544
Actually, I think I might have
heard of this guy.

41:43.588 --> 41:44.850
-Really?
-Yeah.

41:46.199 --> 41:49.942
Keeps this braid woven
with the hair.

41:49.985 --> 41:50.812
People that he eats.

41:53.162 --> 41:54.729
-Christ.
-It's like eight feet long.

41:56.557 --> 41:57.645
[Lee] That's a choice.

41:57.689 --> 41:59.168
We don't have to be like that.

42:00.822 --> 42:01.910
Why didn't you tag along
with him?

42:03.346 --> 42:04.347
[Maren] Mm...

42:06.611 --> 42:08.743
Something about him.
I don't know.

42:10.049 --> 42:12.181
I think he was tryin' to help.

42:12.225 --> 42:14.575
I profoundly doubt that.

42:14.619 --> 42:16.011
He was creepy, I guess.

42:17.535 --> 42:20.538
Did that dawn on you
before or after

42:20.581 --> 42:23.976
[softly] you ate
Mrs. Herman together?

42:24.019 --> 42:25.238
[waitress] More coffee?

42:25.281 --> 42:26.848
-[clears throat] Yes, please.
-Okay.

42:29.764 --> 42:31.026
Can I get anything else
for you guys?

42:31.070 --> 42:32.158
That's all right.
That's good, thanks.

42:32.201 --> 42:33.551
You're welcome.

42:33.594 --> 42:36.336
-Harmon. Mrs. Harmon.
-Mrs... Mrs. Harmon.

42:36.379 --> 42:37.598
[waitress] Okay.
You're welcome.

42:39.208 --> 42:40.166
Does that help?

42:41.341 --> 42:42.516
Memorizing their names?

42:53.353 --> 42:54.572
[sighs]

42:54.615 --> 42:55.964
Why'd you offer
to bring me along?

42:57.836 --> 42:58.837
You seem nice.

43:03.929 --> 43:06.061
-I am nice.
-Mm.

43:08.498 --> 43:09.499
Do I seem nice?

43:14.722 --> 43:15.723
I'm going to the bathroom.

43:20.728 --> 43:22.164
How do you feel
about sleeping outside?

43:22.861 --> 43:23.688
Okay.

43:27.169 --> 43:28.170
[growls playfully]

43:35.569 --> 43:37.702
[Lee] It'll be cold tonight,
but if we keep this truck,

43:37.745 --> 43:39.704
we'll get a sheet of plywood
for back here.

43:40.835 --> 43:42.968
[Maren] What's in
Kentucky anyway?

43:43.011 --> 43:44.665
[Lee] It's my little sister.

43:44.709 --> 43:46.275
I promised to give her
driving lessons

43:46.319 --> 43:47.625
before she has
to take her test.

43:47.668 --> 43:49.844
[Maren] Mm.
[Lee] She's a good kid.

43:49.888 --> 43:51.498
[Maren] Do you get home often?

43:51.541 --> 43:54.588
[Lee] A little bit.
I left when I was 17.

43:54.632 --> 43:56.372
-[thunder cracking]
-[Maren] How come?

43:56.416 --> 43:58.548
[Lee] I didn't finish school,
which sucks.

43:58.592 --> 43:59.985
I'm guessing
you didn't, either.

44:00.028 --> 44:01.856
Other ways to learn, I guess.

44:36.108 --> 44:37.413
[preacher on radio]
Maybe what other peoples'

44:37.457 --> 44:38.806
weaknesses may be.

44:38.850 --> 44:42.157
That Satan knows
where your weakness is.

44:42.201 --> 44:46.292
I said He knows
where your weakness is.

44:46.335 --> 44:48.120
He knows how to stir you up.

44:49.599 --> 44:51.906
I said He knows
how to stir you up.

44:52.733 --> 44:54.474
And He knows[chuckles]

44:54.517 --> 44:58.913
that one of my weaknesses
that I will confess to

44:58.957 --> 45:03.570
is the ability to hate you
to the bitter end.

45:19.368 --> 45:22.241
We'll stay here tonight.
This is my aunt's place.

45:22.284 --> 45:24.504
She died in March.

45:24.547 --> 45:26.462
My house's on the other side
of that plant.

45:26.506 --> 45:27.812
I can't be seen in town,
though.

45:29.030 --> 45:30.162
You need to know why?

45:32.599 --> 45:33.513
No.

45:34.775 --> 45:36.081
What's gonna happen
to all this stuff?

45:36.124 --> 45:37.473
[Lee] My mom's cleanin' it out.

45:37.517 --> 45:39.084
She's a teacher, though.
She got school.

45:42.522 --> 45:43.784
No, keep that off.

45:43.828 --> 45:45.743
And keep the windows closed
tonight too.

45:45.786 --> 45:47.657
Okay, I'mma take Kayla drivin'
behind the mall.

45:48.267 --> 45:49.790
Hope I don't die.

45:49.834 --> 45:51.052
I'll bring back
some food for us later.

45:51.705 --> 45:52.793
Kayla's your sister?

45:52.837 --> 45:54.490
Yeah. Kay,

45:54.534 --> 45:56.231
Kayla. I call her "idiot "
to her face.

45:56.275 --> 45:58.625
Or "stupid." Or whatever.

45:58.668 --> 46:00.322
You can snoop around if
you want, I won't be offended.

46:01.280 --> 46:02.237
See you later.

46:04.849 --> 46:05.763
Lock the door.

46:06.546 --> 46:07.547
[door closes]

46:10.419 --> 46:11.420
[locks door]

46:58.685 --> 46:59.904
[both laughing]

46:59.947 --> 47:01.079
-[banging on door]
-[girl] Lee, open up

47:01.122 --> 47:02.863
the goddam door, asshole.

47:02.907 --> 47:04.038
I know you're in there.

47:06.040 --> 47:09.348
Man, open up this door, Lee.
Let's go.

47:09.391 --> 47:11.045
[Lee] Why are you banging
on the fucking door?

47:12.133 --> 47:13.091
What the fuck
are you doing here?

47:13.134 --> 47:14.309
Nice work, you motard.

47:14.353 --> 47:15.963
Found this note
you put in my purse.

47:16.007 --> 47:17.791
You're leaving? Already?

47:17.835 --> 47:19.662
Maren, this is Kayla.
Kayla, this is Maren.

47:19.706 --> 47:21.186
You're a fuckin' asshole.

47:21.229 --> 47:23.101
You said that you were gonna
stick around this time.

47:23.144 --> 47:25.190
Something came up.
I gotta head out of town.

47:25.233 --> 47:27.148
I... I don't believe you
anymore, Lee.

47:27.192 --> 47:29.716
I... Where are you always
going anyway?

47:29.759 --> 47:30.891
[Lee] Let's go outside,
come on.

47:31.936 --> 47:33.285
I wanna talk to you outside.

47:36.636 --> 47:38.986
I'm going away
for a little bit,
all right? That's it.

47:39.030 --> 47:40.335
[Kayla] Is that
your girlfriend?

47:40.379 --> 47:41.902
[Lee] That's my friend friend,
all right?

47:41.946 --> 47:43.948
Maybe you can meet her
some other time.

47:43.991 --> 47:45.601
Look, I can't stay, Kayla.

47:45.645 --> 47:47.342
I just wanted to take you
drivin' like I said I would.

47:47.386 --> 47:49.344
[Kayla] I fuckin' hate
that you do this.

47:49.388 --> 47:52.391
You know, Dad did this,
and then he didn't come back.

47:52.434 --> 47:54.306
Don't you know every time you
drive off, we're terrified?

47:54.349 --> 47:56.134
[Lee] I'll be back
in a couple of weeks.

47:56.177 --> 47:57.309
What difference does it make?

47:57.352 --> 47:58.397
[Kayla] You're not
listenin' to me.

47:58.440 --> 48:00.051
[Lee] Yes, I am.
Two weeks tops.

48:00.094 --> 48:02.183
I'm not Dad.
I wouldn't do that.

48:02.227 --> 48:05.099
[Kayla] Is there anything
that you don't lie about?

48:05.143 --> 48:08.276
And you look like a fucking
faggot in that shirt.

48:08.320 --> 48:10.061
Honestly, fuck you, Lee.
Fuck you.

48:10.104 --> 48:12.367
[door opens, slams]

48:14.456 --> 48:16.458
[lee breathing shakily]

48:18.678 --> 48:20.071
[softly] God, fuck it, man.

48:21.986 --> 48:22.987
[exhales heavily]

48:29.950 --> 48:31.473
Let's go tonight.

48:31.517 --> 48:33.345
She's probably gonna tell
my mom that we're here.

48:34.215 --> 48:36.174
If she comes, I...

48:36.217 --> 48:37.697
I wanna spare you that.
[chuckles]

48:38.828 --> 48:39.786
[sighs]

48:44.922 --> 48:47.011
I worked summers here.
I can't get in the safe,

48:47.054 --> 48:49.535
but they keep all the petty
cash in a drawer in the cafe.

48:49.578 --> 48:52.103
[Maren] A cafe?
At a slaughterhouse?

49:03.723 --> 49:05.116
Aren't there guards?

49:05.159 --> 49:06.856
[Lee] Yeah. Dale.

49:06.900 --> 49:08.119
Deaf in both ears.

49:29.967 --> 49:31.838
You be the bank.
[panting]

49:33.318 --> 49:34.362
I wanna show you something.

49:35.711 --> 49:37.409
[cows mooing]

49:37.452 --> 49:39.193
[Lee] The music's supposed
to keep 'em calm.

49:41.717 --> 49:44.503
You ever think about that...

49:46.418 --> 49:50.291
every one of them
has a mom and a dad...

49:52.424 --> 49:56.036
sisters, brothers,
cousins, kids.

49:58.778 --> 49:59.822
Friends even?

50:00.475 --> 50:01.563
[cow moos]

50:02.564 --> 50:03.783
A language.

50:06.786 --> 50:08.135
Listen to them.

50:08.179 --> 50:10.181
[cows continue mooing]

50:15.360 --> 50:17.188
You never told me
what was in Minnesota.

50:18.798 --> 50:19.755
My mom.

50:19.799 --> 50:21.061
She lives there?

50:21.105 --> 50:22.019
I don't know.

50:23.411 --> 50:25.500
I don't even know
if she's still alive.

50:27.241 --> 50:30.766
All I have is the name
of the town that she
was born in.

50:34.988 --> 50:36.859
Could take a while
to track her down, you know.

50:38.644 --> 50:39.906
It might even be a dead end.

50:41.951 --> 50:42.952
It's all I have.

50:45.259 --> 50:46.565
Then that's where we'll start.

50:49.611 --> 50:50.525
I can take you...

50:52.049 --> 50:53.093
if you want.
It's a lot of driving,

50:53.137 --> 50:54.660
but I'm up for it, if you are.

50:56.357 --> 50:58.359
We could take our time.
See the country.

50:59.534 --> 51:01.623
Well, Missouri
and Iowa anyway.

51:05.540 --> 51:07.716
-Never been to either.
-[chuckles softly]

51:35.353 --> 51:37.181
[indistinct chatter on radio]

51:54.633 --> 51:57.114
[on radio]
♪ Amarillo by mornin'♪

51:58.463 --> 52:00.943
[singing along]
♪ Up from San Antone♪

52:02.467 --> 52:05.426
♪ Everything that I got♪

52:05.470 --> 52:08.603
♪ Is just what I've got on♪

52:11.040 --> 52:12.259
Whoo-hoo!

52:41.245 --> 52:42.637
[Maren] What was
your first time like?

52:45.379 --> 52:47.294
[smacks lips]
It was a babysitter.

52:47.338 --> 52:48.991
-Mine too.
-Really?

52:50.558 --> 52:51.603
What was it like?

52:54.780 --> 52:55.824
A rush.

52:57.304 --> 52:58.436
I could feel
every blood vessel

52:58.479 --> 53:00.089
like spider-webbing
through me.

53:02.570 --> 53:04.703
Felt like some kind
of weird new superhero.

53:04.746 --> 53:05.573
[chuckles softly]

53:06.531 --> 53:08.576
What about afterward?

53:08.620 --> 53:10.274
What'd you feel about it?
What'd you think?

53:11.536 --> 53:13.059
-I don't remember after.
-[scoffs]

53:14.452 --> 53:16.018
That's bullshit.

53:16.062 --> 53:18.499
Hey, I'm not just gonna
tell you what you wanna hear.

53:18.543 --> 53:20.153
You asked me a question,
I gotta answer it.

53:22.851 --> 53:24.679
Would you do
something with me?

53:24.723 --> 53:26.551
-Listen to something with me?
-Yeah.

53:26.594 --> 53:27.813
[vehicle approaching]

53:35.516 --> 53:37.562
Whoo! I told you
they'd be back here.

53:37.605 --> 53:38.519
[both laugh]

53:41.305 --> 53:43.263
-Hey.
-Hey.

53:43.307 --> 53:44.873
I saw you guys down at
the swimming hole before.

53:44.917 --> 53:47.180
Oh, yeah, we saw some people
down there too.

53:47.224 --> 53:49.008
You were up there
on those rocks.

53:50.227 --> 53:51.271
Up, uh...

53:51.315 --> 53:52.272
Upwind of us.

53:53.273 --> 53:54.100
You get me?

53:54.970 --> 53:56.842
Don't worry, we're friendly.

53:56.885 --> 53:59.758
I'm Jake. That's, uh, Bradley.

53:59.801 --> 54:02.587
Goddamn, my name is Brad, man.
Call me what I want.

54:02.630 --> 54:04.806
Nice to meet you, Brad.
Nice to meet you, Jake.

54:04.850 --> 54:07.679
I'm Leon. That's Maggie.

54:07.722 --> 54:09.158
You just passing through?

54:09.202 --> 54:11.117
Yeah, just passing through.
Is that a problem?

54:11.160 --> 54:12.640
We're not here to run you out.

54:12.684 --> 54:14.642
We thought you might be
in need of some beer.

54:15.164 --> 54:16.296
We got you.

54:16.340 --> 54:17.558
[Jake] Not many
come through here.

54:18.646 --> 54:20.257
-What do you say?
-[sighs softly]

54:22.476 --> 54:24.565
I'm into this now, right?

54:26.437 --> 54:29.048
Pulling meat,
bones comin' out, you know.

54:30.615 --> 54:31.485
[can pops open]

54:32.921 --> 54:35.663
And I start feeling watched.

54:35.707 --> 54:39.319
I look around and at first,
I don't see him 'cause he's...

54:39.363 --> 54:41.495
he's standing so still
in the trees,

54:41.539 --> 54:44.324
but then I spot him.
I'm like, "What the fuck?"

54:44.368 --> 54:46.500
I mean, I look like
the red devil at this point.

54:46.544 --> 54:48.589
He's just watching me
like I'm...

54:48.633 --> 54:49.590
[Brad laughs]

54:50.722 --> 54:52.550
...Doug fuckin' Henning.

54:52.593 --> 54:54.508
[gasping spookily]

54:56.597 --> 54:58.556
[jake and brad laughing]

55:00.862 --> 55:02.777
I'm already on my feet,
and I'm runnin' at him,

55:02.821 --> 55:04.823
and he pulls
a fuckin' pistol on me.

55:06.433 --> 55:08.130
Turns out
he's an off-duty cop.

55:08.174 --> 55:09.480
-First year on the force.
-We did

55:09.523 --> 55:11.264
say we weren't gonna
tell nobody about that.

55:11.308 --> 55:12.439
Oh, right, right.

55:13.092 --> 55:14.049
So, he's a cop.

55:15.616 --> 55:17.096
[Brad chuckles]

55:17.139 --> 55:19.272
I think he's gonna
take me down. But he's just...

55:20.665 --> 55:21.927
he's just looking at me.

55:23.015 --> 55:24.321
And what did I say?

55:24.364 --> 55:27.062
He said, "Do me now
or get the fuck gone

55:27.106 --> 55:28.847
"'cause he ain't gonna be
no fun to eat cold."

55:28.890 --> 55:30.892
-[both laughing]
-I love it.

55:33.025 --> 55:34.853
[cackling]

55:39.771 --> 55:40.728
So he says...

55:43.383 --> 55:46.560
"Go on, back to it. Mm-hmm.

55:46.604 --> 55:48.257
"I gotta get
a better look at this."

55:49.302 --> 55:50.172
[smacks lips]

55:50.216 --> 55:51.913
[chuckles] So, uh...

55:53.437 --> 55:56.048
I suddenly feel him
right there,

55:57.658 --> 55:59.356
crouched down,
gettin' a better look.

56:00.574 --> 56:02.228
He doesn't smell
like an Eater.

56:04.186 --> 56:06.406
But there he is.

56:09.975 --> 56:11.803
So I ask if he wants some.

56:14.675 --> 56:17.417
And damned
if he don't nod all serious

56:17.461 --> 56:20.420
like a food-stamp kid
on samples day.

56:20.464 --> 56:21.421
-Yeah.
-[Jake] So you know

56:21.465 --> 56:22.291
what I gave him?

56:27.601 --> 56:28.733
You're not one of us?

56:37.481 --> 56:42.877
Abso-fucking-lutely normal
he is! [laughs]

56:42.921 --> 56:46.664
-Well, uh, clearly not normal.
-[laughs]

56:48.187 --> 56:50.668
Hasn't had his Full Bones yet.
But, uh...

56:52.409 --> 56:54.149
I reckon that's
coming soon enough.

56:55.455 --> 56:56.543
"Full Bones"?

56:59.938 --> 57:02.157
When you eat the whole thing.
Bones and all.

57:03.985 --> 57:05.030
You ain't done that yet?

57:07.206 --> 57:08.425
That's a big fucking deal.

57:09.208 --> 57:10.688
It's like your first time.

57:13.952 --> 57:14.822
There's...

57:15.954 --> 57:19.131
before Bones and all,

57:19.174 --> 57:20.480
and then there's after.

57:21.873 --> 57:22.787
That's bullshit.

57:24.702 --> 57:26.747
It's impossible,
what you're talking about.

57:26.791 --> 57:28.314
How many people
have you eaten?

57:32.884 --> 57:33.972
[Jake] I count three.

57:35.539 --> 57:36.670
Yes, miss.

57:37.758 --> 57:38.585
Three people.

57:39.543 --> 57:41.283
And you didn't have to?

57:41.327 --> 57:42.850
You don't have to do this?

57:45.331 --> 57:46.680
Kind of a groupie, I guess.

57:49.335 --> 57:50.945
-Jesus Christ.
-You okay?

57:50.989 --> 57:53.426
Jake's teaching me
how to smell other Eaters.

57:54.166 --> 57:55.210
No, he's not.

57:56.734 --> 57:58.213
You don't think he can do it?

58:02.914 --> 58:03.958
[Brad] Is she all right?

58:04.002 --> 58:05.569
[indistinct conversation]

58:09.181 --> 58:11.749
[Brad] Whoa. Fuck. Fuck.

58:13.228 --> 58:14.969
She's lucky
she's got you to help.

58:15.013 --> 58:16.144
[urinating]

58:17.015 --> 58:18.233
God.

58:18.277 --> 58:19.670
He's the one who needs
the help, Brad.

58:21.498 --> 58:22.890
[chuckles]

58:22.934 --> 58:24.762
You can see it a mile away.

58:26.981 --> 58:29.331
You remind me
of every junkie I ever met.

58:31.029 --> 58:33.161
You look like the kind
that's convinced himself

58:33.205 --> 58:34.598
he's got this under his thumb.

58:37.078 --> 58:39.733
But you pull on
one little thread and...

58:41.082 --> 58:42.910
[mimics swishing]

58:47.828 --> 58:51.658
But maybe love
will set you free, man.

58:54.356 --> 58:55.401
[Jake chuckles]

58:56.271 --> 59:00.580
Maybe love will set you

59:01.929 --> 59:03.496
free.

59:05.237 --> 59:07.239
[guffawing]

59:10.721 --> 59:12.940
[unsettling music playing]

59:19.512 --> 59:21.514
[snoring]

59:39.358 --> 59:40.228
[door shuts gently]

1:00:05.036 --> 1:00:06.167
Lee, Lee.

1:00:06.559 --> 1:00:08.169
What?

1:00:08.213 --> 1:00:09.475
-What?
-Look. Look, look, look.

1:00:09.997 --> 1:00:11.346
[groans]

1:00:11.390 --> 1:00:13.000
[unsettling music
intensifying]

1:00:17.352 --> 1:00:18.440
Go, go, go, go, go, go.

1:00:21.835 --> 1:00:23.445
[yells]

1:00:57.523 --> 1:00:58.655
[laughs]

1:01:02.746 --> 1:01:04.399
[ride passengers screaming]

1:01:12.233 --> 1:01:13.191
[vendor] Hot dogs!

1:01:18.587 --> 1:01:20.067
[man] Roll up. Roll up.

1:01:20.111 --> 1:01:21.808
[lively chatter]

1:01:46.050 --> 1:01:47.616
I'm hungry, Lee.

1:01:51.708 --> 1:01:52.883
We should do that
right over there.

1:01:52.926 --> 1:01:54.058
Yeah, we have four tickets.

1:01:54.101 --> 1:01:55.189
-Okay.
-Yes.

1:01:57.626 --> 1:02:00.281
[man 1] Step right up.
We've got big prizes.

1:02:00.325 --> 1:02:01.848
[man 2] Three tickets,
three tries.

1:02:01.892 --> 1:02:03.807
Three tickets, three tries.

1:02:03.850 --> 1:02:04.721
Who wants to play?

1:02:14.992 --> 1:02:16.733
[man 2] Three tickets,
three tries.

1:02:16.776 --> 1:02:17.734
[boy] Can I play?

1:02:18.735 --> 1:02:20.171
You're wasting your money.

1:02:20.214 --> 1:02:22.347
[rock song playing
on speakers]

1:02:23.565 --> 1:02:24.610
Come on.

1:02:33.184 --> 1:02:34.359
-[clang]
-Ah.

1:02:34.402 --> 1:02:36.013
I won. I won.

1:02:36.056 --> 1:02:37.318
No, you didn't, little man.

1:02:38.493 --> 1:02:40.104
[boy] But... But it's in a can.

1:02:42.236 --> 1:02:43.368
What does that mean?

1:02:43.411 --> 1:02:44.891
What you just did.
No underhand.

1:02:44.935 --> 1:02:46.327
But that other kid did it.

1:02:46.371 --> 1:02:48.590
You can read, can't you?

1:02:48.634 --> 1:02:50.984
Now go on. Unless you got
three more tickets.

1:02:53.291 --> 1:02:55.119
Hey, man.

1:02:55.162 --> 1:02:57.469
You tryin' to win one
for your girlfriend?
I saw you walk up.

1:02:57.512 --> 1:02:58.905
Oh, no,
that's not my girlfriend.

1:02:58.949 --> 1:03:01.255
That's just, uh, a friend,
you know. [chuckles]

1:03:07.784 --> 1:03:09.220
-[CLANG]
-Nice.

1:03:09.263 --> 1:03:11.396
- Wow.
- Can I get another one
if I sink it again?

1:03:11.439 --> 1:03:13.137
You're not supposed to.

1:03:13.180 --> 1:03:14.965
But, uh, no one has to know.

1:03:22.015 --> 1:03:23.190
Damn.

1:03:23.234 --> 1:03:24.235
Disappoint.

1:03:24.626 --> 1:03:26.324
Hmm.

1:03:26.367 --> 1:03:28.326
What's there to do around here
besides this dumbass carnival?

1:03:29.936 --> 1:03:31.285
After my friend leaves,
I mean.

1:03:36.900 --> 1:03:38.031
I close up at 11:00.

1:03:38.858 --> 1:03:40.294
I got some weed in my car.

1:03:40.338 --> 1:03:41.295
Hell, yeah.

1:03:42.557 --> 1:03:44.255
-One more?
-Really?

1:03:44.298 --> 1:03:45.125
Yeah.

1:03:50.348 --> 1:03:51.740
-Damn. [laughs]
-Damn.

1:03:58.008 --> 1:03:58.835
Lucky, lucky.

1:04:03.709 --> 1:04:05.493
My luck's not
gonna run out, is it?

1:04:06.103 --> 1:04:06.973
No, man.

1:04:08.148 --> 1:04:09.193
I'll see that it don't.

1:04:10.672 --> 1:04:11.630
I'll see you in an hour?

1:04:13.893 --> 1:04:14.720
Yeah, you will.

1:04:17.941 --> 1:04:19.899
[Maren's father on tape]
I haven't thought much
beyond this tape.

1:04:21.335 --> 1:04:22.902
I can't.

1:04:22.946 --> 1:04:24.295
I don't know
what's going to happen to you

1:04:24.338 --> 1:04:26.863
or what should happen to you.

1:04:26.906 --> 1:04:31.737
I wake up nights sick to death
wondering and hoping.

1:04:31.780 --> 1:04:33.565
Hoping that whatever
troubles you is over,

1:04:33.608 --> 1:04:36.742
and that if there is
a God in Heaven,

1:04:36.785 --> 1:04:38.265
that you're just
a regular girl

1:04:38.309 --> 1:04:41.834
with... regular problems
and regular pain,

1:04:41.878 --> 1:04:43.662
and that you stop
wanting things

1:04:43.705 --> 1:04:45.882
you shouldn't want, Maren.

1:04:45.925 --> 1:04:48.885
And that your heart
has a chance.

1:04:50.277 --> 1:04:51.235
[tape button clicks]

1:04:55.717 --> 1:04:57.589
I knew that's how
it would end.

1:04:58.329 --> 1:04:59.634
"I hope you get better."

1:05:02.333 --> 1:05:04.683
Maybe he's right,
maybe I should pray

1:05:04.726 --> 1:05:06.598
that I wake up one day

1:05:06.641 --> 1:05:08.165
to find they built
a maze around me.

1:05:08.208 --> 1:05:09.035
Don't say that.

1:05:10.428 --> 1:05:11.342
Don't.

1:05:13.953 --> 1:05:14.911
He's wrong.

1:05:18.915 --> 1:05:19.785
He's wrong.

1:05:22.657 --> 1:05:23.745
[Lee sighs]

1:05:25.312 --> 1:05:26.748
What happened to your dad?

1:05:28.011 --> 1:05:29.099
You never say anything.

1:05:30.927 --> 1:05:31.840
Nothing good.

1:05:33.494 --> 1:05:34.887
Just a waste.

1:05:34.931 --> 1:05:36.889
-[door shuts in distance]
-[soft footsteps]

1:05:39.152 --> 1:05:41.024
Except in my case,
I gave him the tape.

1:05:42.025 --> 1:05:43.287
[footsteps approaching]

1:05:48.596 --> 1:05:49.728
Just give me
a couple of minutes.

1:06:12.142 --> 1:06:13.491
You made it.

1:06:13.534 --> 1:06:15.145
-[Lee] This is a good spot.
-Yeah, it's not bad.

1:06:15.188 --> 1:06:16.320
[Lee] There's no one here.

1:06:16.363 --> 1:06:17.625
-[man] Is that you?
-[Lee] Yeah.

1:06:17.669 --> 1:06:18.800
-[man] It's a nice truck.
-[Lee] Great, huh?

1:06:18.844 --> 1:06:20.193
[man] Yeah, she is.
I'm parked up there.

1:06:20.237 --> 1:06:21.064
Do you smoke?

1:06:23.762 --> 1:06:24.763
What are you laughing about?

1:06:26.025 --> 1:06:27.287
-Do you smoke weed too?
-[Lee] Yeah.

1:06:37.341 --> 1:06:38.907
[man chuckles]
You kinky fucker.

1:06:40.997 --> 1:06:42.128
[both laughing]

1:06:44.522 --> 1:06:45.479
[rustling]

1:06:54.836 --> 1:06:55.924
[man moaning]

1:06:58.014 --> 1:06:59.145
[man] Oh, yeah.

1:06:59.189 --> 1:07:01.060
Faster, man.
Jerk it faster. Come on.

1:07:01.104 --> 1:07:03.802
I'm close, yeah.
Yeah, like that.

1:07:03.845 --> 1:07:05.325
[man breathing rapidly]

1:07:07.588 --> 1:07:08.720
Come on, come on, faster, man.

1:07:08.763 --> 1:07:10.591
Faster, faster.
[inhales sharply]

1:07:15.335 --> 1:07:16.249
Oh, yeah.

1:07:17.337 --> 1:07:19.557
[unnerving music playing]

1:07:20.123 --> 1:07:21.341
Oh, fuck!

1:07:22.560 --> 1:07:23.430
Oh.

1:07:28.522 --> 1:07:30.176
[man breathing rapidly]

1:07:31.264 --> 1:07:32.787
Faster, jerk it faster, man.
Come on.

1:07:35.094 --> 1:07:37.227
Yeah, I'm close. I'm close.

1:07:37.270 --> 1:07:38.837
Just like that.

1:07:38.880 --> 1:07:41.666
I'm close, I'm close.
Here it comes. Here it comes.

1:07:41.709 --> 1:07:43.059
That sure feels... [gasps]

1:07:44.147 --> 1:07:46.018
-[body thuds]
-[Lee breathing heavily]

1:07:47.367 --> 1:07:50.240
[man choking and gurgling]

1:07:50.283 --> 1:07:52.720
-[Lee panting]
-[gagging]

1:07:56.159 --> 1:07:57.986
[munching]

1:08:16.179 --> 1:08:17.658
[radio host]
The world in the spring

1:08:17.702 --> 1:08:19.530
and a new skateboard
from Bikes Unlimited.

1:08:19.573 --> 1:08:21.314
[tuning radio]

1:08:21.358 --> 1:08:23.882
[radio host 2] Don't you love
the smell of black rubber?

1:08:28.495 --> 1:08:30.018
Maybe not.

1:08:30.062 --> 1:08:32.717
It's an acquired taste.

1:08:32.760 --> 1:08:34.588
Some people
never get used to it.

1:08:35.372 --> 1:08:36.851
Don't really understand.

1:08:39.332 --> 1:08:41.029
Oh, you can work your way up.

1:08:47.384 --> 1:08:49.386
[radio chatter
continues indistinctly]

1:08:50.865 --> 1:08:52.867
What's wrong?

1:08:52.911 --> 1:08:54.608
[Lee] That's the place
listed on his license,

1:08:54.652 --> 1:08:55.870
but the lights are on.

1:08:58.264 --> 1:08:59.744
I'm gonna go back
and see if anyone's there.

1:08:59.787 --> 1:09:01.963
No, no, I'll go, I'll go.
You have blood on you.

1:09:03.443 --> 1:09:05.750
I cleaned up.
He had wipes in the car.

1:09:05.793 --> 1:09:07.055
You can take them if you want.

1:09:11.059 --> 1:09:12.800
I'll see what I can see
from the yard.

1:09:15.890 --> 1:09:16.761
Okay.

1:09:21.896 --> 1:09:25.117
[radio host 2] All black.
Completely hidden.

1:09:26.727 --> 1:09:29.991
In my black cocoon,
I'm where no one can find me.

1:09:54.364 --> 1:09:55.800
[Maren panting]

1:09:57.367 --> 1:09:58.368
Maren, you okay?

1:10:00.283 --> 1:10:01.240
What are you doing?

1:10:05.070 --> 1:10:07.551
What? Oh, Christ.

1:10:07.594 --> 1:10:08.943
Okay, we didn't know.

1:10:09.988 --> 1:10:12.208
Hey, we didn't know,
okay? [tuts]

1:10:18.475 --> 1:10:19.693
[woman 1] Is he back?

1:10:19.737 --> 1:10:21.739
[woman 2] No!
Something's wrong, Mom!

1:10:21.782 --> 1:10:23.262
All right, we gotta go.
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

1:10:23.306 --> 1:10:24.698
Focus, focus.
Come on, let's go.

1:10:43.935 --> 1:10:47.939
[radio host] Only there
did civilization arise.

1:10:47.982 --> 1:10:51.029
Now, it's not my intention
to give a history lesson,

1:10:51.072 --> 1:10:53.553
but I believe it's important
to remind ourselves

1:10:53.597 --> 1:10:55.033
that in dealing
with the economy,

1:10:55.076 --> 1:10:57.035
we're dealing with
human creativity.

1:10:57.992 --> 1:10:59.429
This insight has represented

1:10:59.472 --> 1:11:01.692
the underpinning of
our economic expansion.

1:11:02.910 --> 1:11:04.347
There wasn't
a car seat, Maren.

1:11:05.565 --> 1:11:06.871
He wasn't wearing
a wedding ring.

1:11:09.395 --> 1:11:10.570
We should feel something.

1:11:11.441 --> 1:11:12.877
'Cause we murder people.

1:11:12.920 --> 1:11:15.140
We steal their stuff,
we move the fuck on,

1:11:15.183 --> 1:11:16.620
and we ruin lives
that we don't even see.

1:11:16.663 --> 1:11:18.012
Come on, why are we talking
about it like this?

1:11:18.056 --> 1:11:19.884
We gotta do this!
We have to do it!

1:11:20.711 --> 1:11:22.452
[sniffles]

1:11:22.495 --> 1:11:24.541
[Maren]
Talking about the future,

1:11:24.584 --> 1:11:26.934
talking about being
a friend to yourself.

1:11:26.978 --> 1:11:29.763
You don't have that.
This is too much.

1:11:31.417 --> 1:11:35.769
No, we got
60, 70 years of this?

1:11:39.382 --> 1:11:40.731
How dare you make this harder.

1:11:50.393 --> 1:11:51.916
Maren, what do I...
What am I supposed...

1:11:52.395 --> 1:11:53.787
How do I get you out of this?

1:11:53.831 --> 1:11:54.962
What am I supposed to say
right now?

1:11:57.225 --> 1:11:58.270
Just drive.

1:11:58.879 --> 1:12:01.317
Right. All right.

1:12:13.764 --> 1:12:15.722
[Maren breathing heavily]

1:12:20.553 --> 1:12:21.772
[gasping]

1:12:24.644 --> 1:12:27.081
[Lee] You were dreaming.
We're almost there.

1:12:28.909 --> 1:12:29.997
[chuckles]

1:12:34.437 --> 1:12:35.960
[patrons chattering]

1:12:38.484 --> 1:12:41.835
Uh, do have a telephone book?
The one outside's missing.

1:12:42.270 --> 1:12:43.402
Uh...

1:12:43.446 --> 1:12:45.709
I'm looking for someone
in Bagley.

1:12:45.752 --> 1:12:48.059
Oh. This is for
the county, sweetie.

1:12:56.633 --> 1:12:58.069
[breathing heavily]

1:12:59.723 --> 1:13:01.072
[Maren] Thanks.

1:13:04.423 --> 1:13:05.337
There.

1:13:14.999 --> 1:13:17.088
-I'll come with you.
-No, stay here.

1:13:29.622 --> 1:13:31.755
Excuse me?
Are you Barbara Kerns?

1:13:40.459 --> 1:13:42.418
Wait, wait. Ms. Kerns.
Ms. Kerns.

1:13:42.940 --> 1:13:44.332
I'm Maren Yearly.

1:13:44.637 --> 1:13:45.508
Maren.

1:13:47.031 --> 1:13:48.728
I've traveled a very long way.

1:13:57.563 --> 1:13:59.260
Oh, they didn't marry.

1:13:59.304 --> 1:14:00.740
Hmm. Yeah, we wondered.

1:14:01.480 --> 1:14:02.307
Huh.

1:14:04.135 --> 1:14:08.139
My husband, uh,
he died years ago.

1:14:08.182 --> 1:14:09.793
Throat cancer.

1:14:09.836 --> 1:14:12.186
-Sorry.
-Mm.

1:14:12.230 --> 1:14:14.058
Sorry to surprise you
like this.

1:14:16.060 --> 1:14:18.715
You didn't know your daughter
had a child, I guess.

1:14:19.672 --> 1:14:21.326
No.

1:14:21.369 --> 1:14:23.981
No. When she wanted
to get married,

1:14:24.547 --> 1:14:25.765
we didn't agree.

1:14:26.853 --> 1:14:29.900
So, it drove her away. Yeah.

1:14:32.859 --> 1:14:34.644
Where did she meet my dad?

1:14:36.428 --> 1:14:37.429
He didn't say?

1:14:38.952 --> 1:14:40.780
He wouldn't say
anything about her.

1:14:42.129 --> 1:14:43.043
Ah.

1:14:44.001 --> 1:14:45.959
Hmm. Mm.

1:14:48.092 --> 1:14:49.049
[sighs]

1:14:57.580 --> 1:15:00.496
They met in college.
Down in Mankato.

1:15:01.671 --> 1:15:02.846
She finished two years

1:15:02.889 --> 1:15:04.543
before he talked her
into leaving.

1:15:06.327 --> 1:15:08.678
Did he drive you here?
Is he outside?

1:15:08.721 --> 1:15:11.071
No. He's in Maryland.

1:15:14.684 --> 1:15:16.686
Does he know you're here?

1:15:16.729 --> 1:15:18.339
Yeah, he let me know
where to find you.

1:15:19.515 --> 1:15:20.864
So you haven't run away?

1:15:21.473 --> 1:15:22.561
No.

1:15:22.605 --> 1:15:23.693
My dad thinks that

1:15:23.736 --> 1:15:24.955
I'm old enough
to live on my own.

1:15:25.825 --> 1:15:27.610
Oh. Uh-huh.

1:15:27.653 --> 1:15:30.526
Well, if you're looking for
a home with your mother,

1:15:31.875 --> 1:15:32.832
um,

1:15:33.616 --> 1:15:35.748
I'm sorry to tell you

1:15:35.792 --> 1:15:38.229
that she...
she's no longer with us.

1:15:41.232 --> 1:15:42.886
What? When?

1:15:42.929 --> 1:15:44.452
It's a lot of years now,

1:15:44.496 --> 1:15:46.890
and it's nothing
I wanna tell you about.

1:15:46.933 --> 1:15:48.369
I hope you can respect that.

1:15:48.413 --> 1:15:49.545
Well, I'm her daughter.

1:15:50.807 --> 1:15:52.635
Yep. Makes sense now.

1:15:52.678 --> 1:15:56.769
Why she came back so bereaved.
That's the word.

1:15:57.901 --> 1:16:00.164
And she wouldn't tell us
anything, either.

1:16:01.426 --> 1:16:05.430
Oh, it's just so much hiding
in one family.

1:16:06.910 --> 1:16:09.303
I'm sorry you had to be
the child of it all.

1:16:11.784 --> 1:16:13.873
Wait. What was
she like as a child?

1:16:16.441 --> 1:16:17.442
Hmm.

1:16:23.709 --> 1:16:25.755
Wow. She was your only child?

1:16:25.798 --> 1:16:27.583
[Barbara] Well, not even ours.

1:16:27.626 --> 1:16:30.194
Bob and I never could have
babies of our own.

1:16:31.456 --> 1:16:33.240
But then we heard
about Janelle.

1:16:34.111 --> 1:16:35.591
She'd been left behind

1:16:35.634 --> 1:16:38.158
a sheriff's station
in Bemidji.

1:16:38.202 --> 1:16:40.030
It was in the paper.

1:16:40.073 --> 1:16:42.685
You know anything
about her biological parents?

1:16:42.728 --> 1:16:43.903
No, nothing.

1:16:43.947 --> 1:16:46.123
Except what they did
to their baby.

1:16:46.166 --> 1:16:48.691
I mean, she could have froze,
you know.

1:16:48.734 --> 1:16:50.475
It's cold here all the time.

1:16:52.782 --> 1:16:54.348
My mother...

1:16:54.392 --> 1:16:57.003
You can, you know, take those
photos if you want 'em.

1:16:57.047 --> 1:16:58.352
Did she ever hurt anyone?

1:17:00.093 --> 1:17:01.617
What kind of question is that?

1:17:03.270 --> 1:17:06.883
I bet she did. I know she did.

1:17:06.926 --> 1:17:08.798
I don't know what you had
to do to cover it up

1:17:08.841 --> 1:17:11.278
or... how much pain
it caused you.

1:17:11.322 --> 1:17:12.932
Stop this. At once.

1:17:12.976 --> 1:17:15.674
Look, you're never
going to see me again, okay?

1:17:15.718 --> 1:17:19.112
You may not be her family
by blood, but I am.

1:17:19.156 --> 1:17:20.287
And I need to know.

1:17:20.331 --> 1:17:23.073
So, please, Mrs. Kerns,
please...

1:17:23.116 --> 1:17:24.640
Then ask her yourself.

1:17:28.295 --> 1:17:29.253
How?

1:17:32.038 --> 1:17:32.952
[sighs]

1:17:33.779 --> 1:17:36.347
Look, I don't know you.

1:17:36.390 --> 1:17:37.783
You gotta understand.

1:17:37.827 --> 1:17:40.003
I didn't know what you wanted
comin' up here.

1:17:40.046 --> 1:17:41.395
And I hope you mean
what you say

1:17:41.439 --> 1:17:43.571
about never coming back here.

1:17:43.615 --> 1:17:48.359
I know that sounds cold,
but I wanna be clear with ya.

1:17:48.402 --> 1:17:50.578
I told you she was
no longer with us,

1:17:50.622 --> 1:17:53.059
but she's not...
she's not dead.

1:17:55.061 --> 1:17:58.325
She's living in a town
called Fergus Falls.

1:17:59.065 --> 1:18:00.458
In a state hospital there.

1:18:00.501 --> 1:18:02.852
And we didn't put her there,

1:18:02.895 --> 1:18:04.549
if that's what
you're thinkin'.

1:18:04.592 --> 1:18:06.594
She signed her own papers.

1:18:06.638 --> 1:18:07.552
[door opens]

1:18:09.510 --> 1:18:10.511
[door closes]

1:18:19.085 --> 1:18:20.347
[panting] Okay.

1:18:30.140 --> 1:18:32.925
Here. My mother's here.

1:19:13.705 --> 1:19:14.662
Do you want me to come in?

1:19:15.576 --> 1:19:16.447
No.

1:19:38.817 --> 1:19:40.906
[nurse] Mrs. Kerns' daughter.

1:19:40.950 --> 1:19:43.953
I sure didn't expect this
when I woke up this morning.

1:19:45.737 --> 1:19:47.086
[muffled shouting]

1:19:48.435 --> 1:19:49.828
[woman screaming]

1:19:49.872 --> 1:19:51.177
[woman 2] Calm down.

1:19:53.658 --> 1:19:54.702
Calm down.

1:19:55.399 --> 1:19:57.836
Is she dangerous?

1:19:57.880 --> 1:20:00.230
It's been many years
since that was a concern.

1:20:00.273 --> 1:20:02.058
[woman 3 crying]

1:20:03.973 --> 1:20:05.322
Why was it ever one?

1:20:05.365 --> 1:20:08.499
Aggression towards the staff.
Self-harm.

1:20:09.500 --> 1:20:10.762
But long ago.

1:20:12.895 --> 1:20:14.853
[keys jingling]

1:20:14.897 --> 1:20:17.247
It's possible she won't
understand who you are.

1:20:18.378 --> 1:20:19.902
She just took
her morning meds,

1:20:19.945 --> 1:20:21.642
so she may nod off anyhow.

1:20:22.208 --> 1:20:24.254
We'll see.

1:20:24.297 --> 1:20:26.430
There's someone here
to see you, Ms. Kerns.

1:20:26.473 --> 1:20:29.389
A surprise.
A wonderful surprise.

1:20:54.719 --> 1:20:55.676
[Maren] It's Maren.

1:20:57.591 --> 1:20:58.418
I'm Maren.

1:21:03.859 --> 1:21:04.903
Can't she speak?

1:21:04.947 --> 1:21:06.078
It's the medication.

1:21:07.775 --> 1:21:10.213
[whimpers, breathing shakily]

1:21:10.256 --> 1:21:11.997
Easy, Ms. Kerns.

1:21:16.436 --> 1:21:17.960
I didn't come with Dad.

1:21:19.962 --> 1:21:22.703
I didn't come with Dad.
Just came by myself.

1:21:25.271 --> 1:21:26.577
Should I give her
the letter, Ms. Kerns?

1:21:26.620 --> 1:21:27.970
I fetched it on the way up.

1:21:28.013 --> 1:21:30.015
[whimpering]

1:21:34.802 --> 1:21:38.545
She wrote this about
15 years ago now, must be.

1:21:38.589 --> 1:21:41.940
I've kept it safe in her file
out there, in case.

1:21:48.991 --> 1:21:49.992
She knew I'd come?

1:21:51.907 --> 1:21:53.082
I'll wait right over here.

1:22:06.095 --> 1:22:11.317
[Janelle] Maren, if a day comes
when you show up here,

1:22:11.361 --> 1:22:15.104
I'll know it's because
your father broke his promise.

1:22:16.192 --> 1:22:18.020
Told you something about me.

1:22:19.412 --> 1:22:21.632
And I'll know why.

1:22:21.675 --> 1:22:24.678
He didn't know what I was
when we married,

1:22:24.722 --> 1:22:28.639
but he figured it out
by the time I had you.

1:22:28.682 --> 1:22:31.772
I promised I would never hurt
either of you,

1:22:31.816 --> 1:22:35.080
but how could we be sure?

1:22:35.124 --> 1:22:38.954
It wasn't easy to leave.
I loved you both so much.

1:22:38.997 --> 1:22:40.912
I thought about
ending my life,

1:22:40.956 --> 1:22:45.569
but I wanted to be here
in case you ever did come.

1:22:47.049 --> 1:22:50.400
All I ever wanted
in this world was love.

1:22:50.443 --> 1:22:53.011
I tried, believed,

1:22:53.055 --> 1:22:55.448
but we can't have it
as we are.

1:22:55.492 --> 1:22:57.973
All we can have
is a little space,

1:22:58.016 --> 1:23:02.238
with bars or a door
that locks.

1:23:02.281 --> 1:23:05.241
[tearfully] I'm sorry
for that, Little Yearly.

1:23:06.546 --> 1:23:09.680
For all the things
I didn't do for you

1:23:09.723 --> 1:23:13.553
and for the one thing
I still can.

1:23:14.424 --> 1:23:15.903
The world of love

1:23:15.947 --> 1:23:18.515
-wants no monsters in it.
-[breathing heavily]

1:23:23.607 --> 1:23:25.609
So let me help you out of it.

1:23:25.652 --> 1:23:27.828
-[growling]
-[Maren gasping]

1:23:31.615 --> 1:23:32.877
[Maren] No! Help me!

1:23:32.920 --> 1:23:34.835
Ms. Kerns, calm down!

1:23:35.619 --> 1:23:37.490
Maren, die.

1:23:39.275 --> 1:23:40.319
[Maren] Let me out. Let me out.

1:23:40.363 --> 1:23:42.060
Press the button
on the door. Go!

1:23:44.062 --> 1:23:45.455
[gasping]

1:23:45.498 --> 1:23:48.023
[blubbering]

1:23:52.114 --> 1:23:53.289
[door rattling]

1:23:55.030 --> 1:23:56.901
I can't open the door.
I can't open the door.

1:23:56.944 --> 1:23:58.207
[Lee] Sorry, sorry.
Here we go, here we go.

1:23:58.250 --> 1:24:00.513
[Maren] I can't
fucking with the door.

1:24:00.557 --> 1:24:01.862
[Lee] You're good.

1:24:01.906 --> 1:24:03.821
[Maren] She's one of us.

1:24:03.864 --> 1:24:05.301
She's one of us
but she's fucking nuts.

1:24:05.344 --> 1:24:07.129
She ate her own fucking hands.

1:24:07.172 --> 1:24:08.304
She said she loved my dad.

1:24:08.347 --> 1:24:09.827
She said she wanted
to be a mom.

1:24:10.828 --> 1:24:12.177
She could have stayed.

1:24:12.221 --> 1:24:14.571
She could have told me
what I needed to know.

1:24:14.614 --> 1:24:16.138
But all of this...
Fuck, you know how different

1:24:16.181 --> 1:24:18.488
this would've been if I'd had
one person on my side?

1:24:18.531 --> 1:24:20.664
One person to talk to?

1:24:20.707 --> 1:24:22.100
You know what
I wouldn't have done?

1:24:22.144 --> 1:24:24.581
Maybe, probably half
of what I've fucking done!

1:24:25.495 --> 1:24:27.105
Fuck her. Fuck.

1:24:27.149 --> 1:24:29.151
[Lee] You know,
if she'd stayed,

1:24:29.194 --> 1:24:31.240
she might have hurt you,
Maren. Or worse, you might not
even be here right now.

1:24:33.111 --> 1:24:34.852
Trust me, I know what I'm
talking about with this stuff.

1:24:34.895 --> 1:24:36.549
This is better than
what I went through.

1:24:36.593 --> 1:24:38.290
Please just stop
fucking talking!

1:24:40.031 --> 1:24:41.989
You're pissed off,
and you're scared,
and you feel alone,

1:24:42.033 --> 1:24:43.643
and you don't know what to do
with it all, it's fine.

1:24:43.687 --> 1:24:45.950
If you wanna go at yourself
with that, I can't stop you.

1:24:46.733 --> 1:24:47.734
But don't come at me.

1:24:48.909 --> 1:24:51.173
You slit his throat, Lee.

1:24:51.216 --> 1:24:53.610
-He had a wife. Kids.
-Okay.

1:24:53.653 --> 1:24:55.438
I think you got used
to being locked up

1:24:55.481 --> 1:24:57.266
and invisible and alone,
and now you're
out in the world...

1:24:57.309 --> 1:24:58.789
-Okay, okay.
-...and you're seeing yourself

1:24:58.832 --> 1:25:01.096
for the first time,
and that's freaking you out.

1:25:01.139 --> 1:25:03.141
But you know what?
It's fucking me up too, okay?

1:25:03.185 --> 1:25:05.012
I feel like
I'm seeing myself too.
That's how this works.

1:25:05.056 --> 1:25:06.623
-How what works?
-This!

1:25:06.666 --> 1:25:07.667
Whatever this is.

1:25:11.236 --> 1:25:13.151
Stop. You're wrong,
you're wrong.

1:25:13.195 --> 1:25:14.631
What? About which part
am I wrong?

1:25:14.674 --> 1:25:17.112
I can't be around you anymore.
I can't think.

1:25:17.155 --> 1:25:18.722
Jesus Christ.

1:25:18.765 --> 1:25:20.376
We don't have
many options, Maren.

1:25:20.419 --> 1:25:22.334
Either you eat,
you off yourself,

1:25:22.378 --> 1:25:24.206
or you lock yourself up
like her in there.

1:25:24.249 --> 1:25:25.207
What's it gonna be?

1:25:26.904 --> 1:25:28.514
Why can't you
let me have this?

1:25:30.560 --> 1:25:31.387
[sighs]

1:25:35.217 --> 1:25:36.174
No.

1:25:38.002 --> 1:25:41.310
I'm not going to be her.
I'm not going to be her.

1:25:42.180 --> 1:25:43.486
You can decide no.

1:25:43.529 --> 1:25:46.402
And I'm deciding that
right fucking now.

1:26:50.205 --> 1:26:51.249
I'm just getting gas.

1:26:53.295 --> 1:26:54.252
You have the money.

1:26:58.909 --> 1:27:00.084
[Lee sighs]

1:28:11.155 --> 1:28:12.199
[Lee] Maren!

1:28:15.377 --> 1:28:16.552
Maren!

1:29:13.783 --> 1:29:18.614
[singing]
♪ Beautiful,
beautiful brown eyes♪

